1. Source Control Tools

1.1. Subversion

Install subversion using a standard repository.

Ubuntu:
$ sudo apt-get install subversion

General:
See http://subversion.apache.org/packages.html

1.2. Git

Install git from a standard repository.

Ubuntu:
$ sudo apt-get install git

General:
See http://git-scm.com/downloads


2. D Compiler and Tools

2.1. D Compiler
$ cd ~/tmp
$ git clone https://github.com/D-Programming-Language/installer.git
$ cd installer/linux
$ ./dmd_deb.sh -v"2.058" -m"32"
$ sudo dpkg -i dmd_2.0.58-0_i386.deb

3. Dependencies

3.1. Derelict 2

3.1.1. Download Derelict 2 Source

$ svn co http://svn.dsource.org/projects/derelict/branches/Derelict2
$ cd Derelict2

3.1.2. Build DerelictGL
$ cd DerelictGL
$ PLATFORM=linux DC=dmd make
$ cd ..

3.1.3. Build DerelictSDL
$ cd DerelictSDL
$ PLATFORM=linux DC=dmd make
$ cd ..

3.1.4. Build DerelictUtil
$ cd DerelictUtil
$ PLATFORM=linux DC=dmd make
$ cd ..

3.1.3. Install headers and library files.
$ mkdir -p ~/d/include/
$ cp -r import/* ~/d/include
$ cp -r lib/* ~/d/lib

4.1. Build the project
$ cd dsdl.git
$ dmake